</p>

<h2><%= @number %> is now your JMP number!</h2>

<p>
Success!  Your free 30-day trial has begun.  You may send up to 300 text or
picture messages, or <a href="../upgrade1/">upgrade to a paid account</a> at any
time during this period to receive unlimited text and picture messages for the
duration of the JMP beta, and to keep your JMP number (it will be reclaimed
after the trial if you don't upgrade to a paid account and don't
<a href="https://www.fcc.gov/consumers/guides/porting-keeping-your-phone-number-when-you-change-providers">port</a>
your JMP number to another provider).
</p>

<h3>Sending and receiving text and picture messages</h3>

<p>
Text messages to/from <%= @number %> can be
received/sent from your Jabber ID (<%= @jid %>).
The easiest way to begin using JMP is by texting your JMP number
(<%= @number %>) from another phone.  Alternatively, you can start sending text
messages using <a href="../#sending">the instructions in the FAQ</a>.
</p>

<h3>Making and receiving phone calls</h3>

<p>
During the trial period you may use up to 30 minutes of incoming and outgoing
voice calls.  You can <a href="../upgrade1/">upgrade to a paid account</a> at
any time during this period to receive 120 minutes of incoming and outgoing
calls per month.
</p>

<h4>Making phone calls</h4>

<p>
If you want to make a phone call using your JMP number, you can login to your
JMP SIP account with any SIP client (such as
<a href="https://code.google.com/archive/p/csipsimple/">CSipSimple</a> - we
recommend using its TCP option) with the following credentials and then start
placing calls (this works regardless of the "Receiving" option you choose
below):
</p>

<table style="margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;">
<tr><td>server:</td><td><code><%= @prefix %>.bwapp.bwsip.io</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>user ID:</td><td><code><%= @sip_user %></code></td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding-right:1.5rem;">password:</td>
<td><code><%= @sip_pass %></code></td></tr>
</table>

<p>
If you need to retrieve the above SIP login information later, you can always
<a href="../#support">contact support</a>; we're happy to send you your user ID
or reset your password.
</p>

